                    "updated": "2010-06-23T13:10:01.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41491",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mkliewe",
                        "name": "mkliewe",
                        "displayName": "Michael Kliewe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I would also love to see a change here because I have the problem that I want to send a mail with attachments >100MB, and my php memory limit of 512 MB is exhausted, I think this log is one of the problems. \r\nI would like to disable logging completly, setting MAXIMUM_LOG to 0 is not enough because the big DATA request would be logged anyway into $this->_log and fill up my memory.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mkliewe",
                        "name": "mkliewe",
                        "displayName": "Michael Kliewe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-15T11:35:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-15T11:35:20.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41492",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mkliewe",
                        "name": "mkliewe",
                        "displayName": "Michael Kliewe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Forget the sentence with the big DATA request, I have seen that there are thousands of little log entries instead of one big log entry when sending a big mail.\r\n\r\nBut I would like to disable this log per default because 99% of the users don't need it, it only wastes CPU. If a developer needs the log he can enable it then, but default should be off. Or default of $_maximumLog should be -1 which disable the log. In _addLog there has to be one line \r\n{code}\r\nif ($this->_maximumLog < 0) return;\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mkliewe",
                        "name": "mkliewe",
                        "displayName": "Michael Kliewe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-15T11:55:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-15T11:55:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41547",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Resolved on trunk and will be released in the next major release.\r\n\r\nPlease beware that I'm unsure why originally it was chosen to use a constant for this. If it turns out there was a proper reason for that that's still legit this patch will be reverted.\r\n\r\nIn any case; thank you for reporting this issues and my apologies for the delays in fixing it.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-16T15:05:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-16T15:05:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41550",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=boydjd",
                        "name": "boydjd",
                        "displayName": "Josh Boyd",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Your commit is wrong, getMaximumLog is incorrectly named setMaximumLog.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=boydjd",
                        "name": "boydjd",
                        "displayName": "Josh Boyd",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-16T15:34:25.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-16T15:34:25.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41551",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Should be fixed once again. Thanks.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-16T15:38:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-16T15:38:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41633",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mkliewe",
                        "name": "mkliewe",
                        "displayName": "Michael Kliewe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I checked your commit, Dolf, and I cannot see a possibility to disable the log. Should I create a new issue for that? \r\n\r\nBecause I don't want to log the transaction in production environment, and logging every line is a performance problem, because in my tests when sending a 60MB mail I have 300.000 calls of _addLog and also 300.000 calls of \r\n{code}$this->_log[] = $value;{code}\r\n\r\nBest solution would be to have something like\r\n{code}\/\/ Save request to internal log\r\nif (true == $this->_loggingEnabled) {\r\n    $this->_addLog($request . self::EOL);\r\n}{code}\r\nin both _send() and _receive() so we don't have thousands of function calls.\r\n\r\nPerhaps in ZF 2.0 we could even disable this logging feature by default because only developers need it for debugging, 99% of the users don't need that logging feature in a default installation. This would increase the performance of the component. But this would be a BC.\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mkliewe",
                        "name": "mkliewe",
                        "displayName": "Michael Kliewe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-20T08:13:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-20T08:13:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41634",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=boydjd",
                        "name": "boydjd",
                        "displayName": "Josh Boyd",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Just call setMaximumLog(0) and logging is disabled.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=boydjd",
                        "name": "boydjd",
                        "displayName": "Josh Boyd",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-20T08:40:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-20T08:40:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41636",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mkliewe",
                        "name": "mkliewe",
                        "displayName": "Michael Kliewe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@Josh: I don't see it, could you please tell me the line? There is no \"return\" or something in _addLog(), so the function _addLog() is called every time and an entry is filled into the array $this->_log . You are right that this entry is shifted out on the next call of _addLog(), but it keeps filling the array 300.000 times.\r\n\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mkliewe",
                        "name": "mkliewe",
                        "displayName": "Michael Kliewe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-20T10:16:27.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-20T10:16:27.000+0000"
                }
            ]
